<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910701-0066</DOCNO><DOCID>910701-0066.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Hitachi Zosen Corp.:   Earnings Soared in Year;   Decline in Costs Is Cited</HL><DATE>07/01/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   J.HZO</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)HEAVY MACHINERY, FARM EQUIPMENT (MAC)SHIPBUILDERS OF COMMERCIAL SHIPS (SHP)STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)ALL TRANSPORTATION EQUIPMENT (TRQ)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>FAR EAST (FE)JAPAN (JA)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)</RE><LP>   Hitachi Zosen Corp., a major Japanese ship and heavymachinery manufacturer, said its net profit soared 547.5% inthe year ended March 31, in part because of cost declines.   Net reached 9.28 billion yen ($67.3 million) on sales of355.74 billion yen, compared with year-earlier profit of 1.43billion yen and sales of 343.86 billion. Pretax profit leapedto 14.63 billion yen from 1.92 billion.</LP><TEXT>   The company's cost of sales fell 2.3% and this, coupledwith the sales gain, served to push up profit, companyofficials said.</TEXT></DOC>